oai_dc:dc.dc:title: UNF Environmental Center
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The Environmental Center at the University of North Florida was founded in 2004. Its mission is to develop and foster multidisciplinary education and research related to the environment. The center is governed by an Executive Board representing all five UNF colleges: Arts and Sciences; Business; Computing, Engineering and Construction; Health, Education and Human Services. Collections in this group were developed, constructed, or funded by the UNF Environmental Center.
